  "prompt": "How do I know if someone blocks me on Facebook messenger?",
  "response": "Facebook doesn't explicitly tell you if someone has blocked you on Messenger. However, you can look for a few clues:\n\n**1. You Can't See Their Profile Picture Anymore:**\n\n*   If their profile picture disappears in your Messenger conversation, and you were able to see it before, this is a strong indicator.  Keep in mind that they might have just changed their picture or made it private.  So, look for other clues.\n\n**2. You Can't Send Messages:**\n\n*   **This is the most reliable sign.** If you try to send a message and you see an error message like \"This person isn't receiving messages at this time\" or \"Message Not Sent,\" it's highly likely they've blocked you.\n*   **Important:** Sometimes, network issues or temporary Messenger problems can cause messages to fail. So, try sending the message again later (maybe after a few hours or a day) to see if the problem persists.\n\n**3. You Can't Find Them in Search:**\n\n*   Try searching for their name in the Facebook search bar. If you can't find their profile, it *could* mean they've blocked you, but it could also mean they've deactivated their account or changed their privacy settings significantly.\n\n**4. Shared Groups (Less Reliable):**\n\n*   If you're in a group with the person, you might still see their messages in the group, even if they've blocked you. This doesn't mean they *haven't* blocked you in direct messages.\n\n**5. Check with a Mutual Friend (Most Reliable, but requires asking someone):**\n\n*   If you really need to know, you could ask a mutual friend to see if they can still see the person's profile and send them messages. If your friend can, but you can't, it's almost certain you've been blocked.  This is a bit awkward, so use it as a last resort.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Privacy Settings:** Someone might have adjusted their privacy settings so that only friends of friends can message them, or they might have made their profile harder to find in search. These settings can make it *look* like you've been blocked when you haven't.\n*   **Account Deactivation:** If the person has deactivated their Facebook account, you won't be able to find them or send them messages. This is different from being blocked.\n\n**In Summary:**\n\n*   The most reliable sign of being blocked is not being able to send messages and seeing an error.\n*   No single sign is definitive on its own. Look for a combination of clues.\n*   Consider other possibilities, such as privacy settings or account deactivation.\n\nUltimately, Facebook doesn't give a clear notification of being blocked to avoid conflict and protect the blocker's privacy.  So, you'll have to interpret the clues.\n",
